This paper deals with information theoretic privacy measures and mechanisms, which are commonly studied in the computer security (cs.CR) and information theory (cs.IT) communities. The paper also discusses the use of joint distributions and Lipschitz continuity, which are relevant topics in machine learning (cs.LG), data structures (cs.DS), and databases (cs.DB).
